               <head>Military History of Tipu Sultan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Fatḥ al-mujāhidīn by Ghulām Muḥyī al-Dīn</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85195025 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104964 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010101829" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4510-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on military ethics, strategy, and weaponry by Ghulam Muhyiuddin, first bakhshī of the jaysh kachihrah, written in praise and support of his patron, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_7368495" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50052021" role="pat subject">Tipu Sultan of Mysore</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>This version may differ from the work of the same name and for the same patron by Zayn al-ʿĀbidīn Shūstarī </p>
                        <p>Colophon not dated: written for Mr David Moore by the munshī Mūhan Laʿl of the Barhaman qawm, resident of the Punjab, attending Parsurām Bahādur on the [anti-]Tipu campaign in the Carnatic; completed at TRY KRH</p>
                        <p>Not foliated; estimated 150 folios approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="urd">Persian &amp; Dakhini Urdu</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22036">Fatḥ al-mujāhidīn</title>
